### Working with the `pm` API

Use the `pm` API to write your test under the **Tests** tab in Postman. The `pm.test()` method accepts two parameters -

The first parameter is the name of the test, so it's important to give your test a descriptive name to provide more information in case the test fails.

The second parameter is a function whereby if any assertions within your function fail, then the test will fail.

```
pm.test("Name of the second test", function () {
    // make as many assertions as you'd like as part of this test
    // if any assertion throws an error, this test will fail
    pm.response.to.have.status(200);
    pm.response.to.be.ok;
    pm.response.to.be.json;
});

```

